WEBVTT

00:30.498 --> 00:32.600
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

00:36.737 --> 00:38.172
MMPH.

00:38.172 --> 00:40.741
YOU'RE IN NEED OF CORRECTION,
AREN'T YOU?

00:40.741 --> 00:43.177
[ Muffled ] YEAH.

00:51.786 --> 00:54.355
I MIGHT LEAVE MARKS.

00:54.355 --> 00:56.590
NOT A GREAT IDEA.

00:56.590 --> 00:58.592
THAT'S NOT A NO.

01:04.732 --> 01:06.834
[ SIZZLES ]
MNH! OH!

01:06.834 --> 01:08.769
OHH!

01:08.769 --> 01:10.838
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

01:10.838 --> 01:13.607
THAT'S GOT TO BURN.

01:13.607 --> 01:15.743
LET ME FIX IT.

01:15.743 --> 01:17.578
[ LEATHER CREAKING ]

01:17.578 --> 01:19.547
[ URINE SPLATTERING ]

01:19.547 --> 01:23.184
[ MOANING ]

01:23.184 --> 01:25.252
AHHH.

01:27.755 --> 01:30.791
â™ªâ™ª

01:40.501 --> 01:43.304
[ INDISTINCT CHATTER ]

01:45.306 --> 01:47.208
SEE, WHAT YOU HAVE TO
UNDERSTAND, MICHAEL,

01:47.208 --> 01:49.276
IS THAT THIS IS
A FUCK-UP-FREE ZONE.

01:49.276 --> 01:51.645
GUYS WHO SIT IN CHUCK'S CHAIR
BECOME MAYOR.

01:51.645 --> 01:52.880
GOVERNOR.

01:52.880 --> 01:55.282
WE HAVE TO BE
BEYOND REPROACH.

01:55.282 --> 01:58.586
SO NO TINDER
AT THE GODDAMN OFFICE, OKAY?

02:01.522 --> 02:03.190
[ SCOFFS ]

02:03.190 --> 02:05.826
IT FEELS LIKE YESTERDAY
I WAS TELLING YOU ALL THIS.

02:05.826 --> 02:07.294
MM, 18 MONTHS AGO.
HUH.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.430
ADDED SOME STUFF
OF MY OWN IN THERE.

02:09.430 --> 02:10.831
YEAH. TINDER.
I HEARD.

02:10.831 --> 02:12.466
COME ON.
HE'S WAITING.

02:15.336 --> 02:17.505
WELL, OFF THE RECORD,
THE, UH, ATTORNEY GENERAL'S

02:17.505 --> 02:19.406
ALWAYS HAPPY TO TAKE
MY RECOMMENDATIONS

02:19.406 --> 02:21.275
ON WHO TO APPOINT
TO THE FEDERAL BENCH.

02:22.610 --> 02:24.211
UH-HUH.

02:24.211 --> 02:25.713
VERY GOOD.

02:25.713 --> 02:26.881
THANK YOU.

02:26.881 --> 02:28.349
Sacker: SIR.

02:28.349 --> 02:30.284
OKAY, GUYS.
WHAT DO WE GOT ON DECK?

02:30.284 --> 02:32.253
PROGRESS REPORT ON TWO
OF THE OPEN INVESTIGATIONS.

02:32.253 --> 02:33.220
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

02:33.220 --> 02:35.155
KIM:
Ari Spyros from the S.E.C...

02:35.155 --> 02:36.257
CALL BACK.

02:36.257 --> 02:37.491
...is here.

02:37.491 --> 02:39.293
I'M SORRY, SIR.
HE -- HE WOULDN'T --

02:39.293 --> 02:41.262
IT'S FINE, KIM.
IT'S OKAY. THANK YOU.

02:41.262 --> 02:43.631
WELL, SPYROS.

02:43.631 --> 02:44.899
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

02:44.899 --> 02:46.767
WE'RE NOT INTERVIEWING
RIGHT NOW.

02:46.767 --> 02:48.536
FUNNY. HERE.

02:50.671 --> 02:52.373
THIS GOT YOUR PANTIES
ALL STICKY?

02:52.373 --> 02:53.674
DRENCHED.

02:53.674 --> 02:56.677
SUSPECT TRADING PATTERN
ON PEPSUM PHARMACEUTICALS.

02:56.677 --> 02:57.912
UH-HUH.

02:57.912 --> 03:00.214
ONE OF MY GRUNTS
RIDING THE MIDAS

03:00.214 --> 03:01.815
SPOTTED A DAYS-LONG
BUY SPIKE.

03:01.815 --> 03:03.951
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

03:05.352 --> 03:07.454
YEAH, GET ME SPYROS.

03:07.454 --> 03:09.189
TAKE A LOOK.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.662
YOU CAN ALL STUDY
THE CHARTS,

03:14.662 --> 03:16.730
OR I CAN GIVE YOU
THE ANSWERS TO THE TEST.

03:16.730 --> 03:17.698
PLEASE.

03:17.698 --> 03:19.567
LENNY BOSCO --
OLD OAKS INVESTMENTS.

03:19.567 --> 03:21.669
PETER DECKER --
QUAKER RIDGE FINANCIAL.

03:21.669 --> 03:24.605
DAN MARGOLIS --
CENTURY CAPITAL.

03:24.605 --> 03:25.873
THESE THREE SMALL FIRMS

03:25.873 --> 03:29.209
ALL KNEW EXACTLY WHEN TO BUY
AND WHEN TO SELL THE STOCK.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.511
THEY HAD
INSIDE INFORMATION.

03:30.511 --> 03:32.346
YOU MUST GET PINGS LIKE THAT
EVERY DAY.

03:32.346 --> 03:33.247
WE DO.

03:33.247 --> 03:35.249
SO? GET THEM TALKING
AND FINE THEM.

03:35.249 --> 03:37.484
IT'S BIGGER THAN THAT.

03:37.484 --> 03:42.489
ALL THREE FIRMS HAVE LINKS
TO BOBBY AXELROD.

03:46.560 --> 03:50.497
BOBBY FUCKING AXELROD.
MAN OF THE PEOPLE.

03:52.466 --> 03:55.269
YOU ONLY HAVE THAT EXACT LOOK ON
YOUR FACE WHEN YOU'RE HERE.

03:55.269 --> 03:57.571
THE PIZZA'S JUST
REALLY FUCKING GOOD.

03:57.571 --> 03:58.639
TAKE A BITE.

04:02.910 --> 04:04.645
MMM. IT'S GOOD.

04:04.645 --> 04:06.780
GOOD?
THAT IS A THING OF BEAUTY.

04:06.780 --> 04:09.383
THAT'S WHY WE LIVED IN HERE
WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

04:09.383 --> 04:10.517
HEY.

04:10.517 --> 04:12.820
Bruno: I DON'T USUALLY OPEN
FOR BREAKFAST, GUYS.

04:12.820 --> 04:14.288
YOU WANT ANOTHER?

04:15.456 --> 04:17.691
I DO.

04:17.691 --> 04:19.426
WE WANT 'EM ALL.

04:19.426 --> 04:20.828
ALL?

04:23.564 --> 04:25.466
I WANT TO COME IN
WITH YOU.

04:25.466 --> 04:26.467
PARTNER UP.

04:27.635 --> 04:29.570
WHAT THE FUCK
DID YOU TELL HIM, KID?

04:29.570 --> 04:31.572
I DON'T WANT NO CHARITY.

04:31.572 --> 04:33.273
LOOK, ALL I TOLD HIM
WAS THE TRUTH, BRUNO, OKAY?

04:33.273 --> 04:34.642
THAT I GOT A CALL
FROM A GUY

04:34.642 --> 04:37.044
WHO SAID HE WAS COMING IN HERE
WITH A FALAFEL SHOP,

04:37.044 --> 04:38.679
AND WOULD I CONTRACT
THE REBUILD.

04:38.679 --> 04:40.280
AND WHEN I ASKED YOU
ABOUT IT,

04:40.280 --> 04:42.483
YOU SAID THAT YOU WERE GETTING
SQUEEZED BY A NEW LANDLORD.

04:42.483 --> 04:45.052
AND WHEN I GOT THAT CALL,
I MADE A COUPLE CALLS OF MY OWN.

04:45.052 --> 04:46.820
FALAFEL SHOP
GOES IN THE MALL.

04:46.820 --> 04:48.856
WE LOCK IN YOU IN
ON A 20-YEAR LEASE,

04:48.856 --> 04:50.858
AND I COVER THE OVERAGE.

04:50.858 --> 04:52.993
I-I-I DON'T KNOW, BOBBY.

04:52.993 --> 04:54.561
COME ON.
WHAT IS THERE TO KNOW?

04:54.561 --> 04:56.530
YOU LET ME SLIDE FOR WEEKS
WITHOUT PAYING

04:56.530 --> 04:58.632
WHEN I WAS COMING IN HERE
EVERY DAY AFTER SCHOOL.

04:58.632 --> 05:00.534
THAT WAS JUST 'CAUSE
YOU WERE A GOOD CUSTOMER.

05:00.534 --> 05:02.770
WHICH I WANT TO KEEP BEING.

05:02.770 --> 05:04.071
NOTHING CHANGES.

05:11.412 --> 05:14.014
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

05:14.014 --> 05:16.083
I'D LOVE TO TELL YOU
I KNEW YOU'D GROW UP

05:16.083 --> 05:17.518
TO BECOME WHAT YOU DID,

05:17.518 --> 05:21.655
BUT TO BE HONEST,
I HAD NO IDEA.

05:21.655 --> 05:22.923
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

05:22.923 --> 05:24.658
COME HERE.

05:26.927 --> 05:27.928
THANKS.

05:36.837 --> 05:39.440
Mick: BOBBY, WE ARE READY TO
ROLL ON SOMETHING SWEET.

05:39.440 --> 05:40.708
I THINK YOU'LL
WANT TO PIGGYBACK.

05:40.708 --> 05:41.775
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

05:41.775 --> 05:43.944
LumeTherm POWER GETTING BOUGHT
BY ELECTRIC SUN.

05:43.944 --> 05:45.779
PRICE IS $41.
STOCK'S TRADING AT $35.

05:45.779 --> 05:47.347
WE'RE LOOKING
AT A 17% BUMP

05:47.347 --> 05:48.882
IN TWO WEEKS
WHEN THE DEAL CLOSES.

05:48.882 --> 05:50.451
ANNUALIZED,
THAT'S $442--

05:50.451 --> 05:51.652
I'D LOVE TO SIZE UP.

05:51.652 --> 05:54.388
MAYBE YOU BUY 2 MILLION SHARES
FOR THE MAIN FUND.

05:54.388 --> 05:56.056
SOUNDS ABOUT RIGHT.
GREAT.

05:56.056 --> 05:59.059
SCOTT KAZAWITZ'S NAME IS BEING
FLOATED AS THE NEW CHAIRMAN.

05:59.059 --> 06:00.994
KAZAWITZ.

06:00.994 --> 06:02.796
THAT'S A NEW PIECE
OF INFORMATION.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.631
WELL, THAT'S WHAT
YOU PAY ME FOR.

06:04.631 --> 06:05.799
WHO SAID THIS DEAL
IS GONNA CLOSE?

06:05.799 --> 06:07.067
BEN SAID IT WOULD
THIS MORNING.

06:07.067 --> 06:08.902
ME?
EVERYONE'S SAYING IT.

06:08.902 --> 06:10.037
WHO IS THIS?

06:10.037 --> 06:11.505
MY NEW ANALYST.

06:11.505 --> 06:14.041
WELL, IF WE HIRED YOU,
YOU MUST BE A GENIUS.

06:14.041 --> 06:15.375
YALE?

06:15.375 --> 06:17.044
STANFORD.
THEN WHARTON.

06:17.044 --> 06:18.746
OKAY, STANFORD-WHARTON.

06:18.746 --> 06:21.648
ELECTRIC SUN IS
CONTROLLED BY KAZAWITZ.

06:21.648 --> 06:23.784
HE ALSO OWNS 19.3%
OF LumeTherm

06:23.784 --> 06:25.786
BACKDOORED THROUGH HIS STAKE
IN SOUTHERN WIND.

06:25.786 --> 06:28.589
YOU SEE THAT BLOCK TRADE LAST
THURSDAY COME OUT OF MERRILL?

06:28.589 --> 06:29.656
YEAH. THAT WAS FORTRESS

06:29.656 --> 06:32.092
CASHING OUT THEIR SHORTS
BEFORE THE MERGER.

06:32.092 --> 06:33.861
WASN'T IT?

06:33.861 --> 06:35.996
TRADE WAS AT 12:52,
WHEN EVERYONE WAS AT LUNCH,

06:35.996 --> 06:38.165
WHICH TELLS ME THEY WANTED IT
TO BE MISSED.

06:38.165 --> 06:40.768
YOU GUYS CAUGHT IT,
WHICH IS SOMETHING, I GUESS.

06:40.768 --> 06:42.703
BUT YOU'RE LOOKING AT IT
BACKWARD.

06:42.703 --> 06:44.571
ELECTRIC SUN'S OFFER
WAS JUST A PLOY

06:44.571 --> 06:46.073
TO TEMPORARILY PROP UP
LumeTherm.

06:46.073 --> 06:49.009
TYPICAL KAZAWITZ PLAY TO BAIL
ON A LOSER. HE'S AN ANIMAL.

06:49.009 --> 06:52.412
THE BLOCK TRADE WAS KAZAWITZ
GETTING OUT OF SOUTHERN WIND,

06:52.412 --> 06:53.680
GETTING OUT OF LumeTherm.

06:53.680 --> 06:55.582
HE RODE THE STORY,
NOW HE'S OUT,

06:55.582 --> 06:57.050
WHICH MEANS
YOU NEED TO BE OUT.

06:57.050 --> 06:58.418
IN FACT, SHORT.

06:58.418 --> 07:01.121
IT'LL SLIDE TO $32 AND CHANGE
AFTER WORD BREAKS.

07:01.121 --> 07:02.689
WOW.

07:02.689 --> 07:04.458
THAT'S A GOOD CATCH, AXE.

07:07.161 --> 07:08.996
MY CHOLESTEROL'S
HIGH ENOUGH.

07:08.996 --> 07:11.532
DON'T BUTTER MY ASS, DANZIG.
JUST GET SMARTER.

07:12.966 --> 07:15.736
YOUR READ WAS GOOD
WITH THE INFORMATION YOU HAD.

07:15.736 --> 07:18.005
YOU'RE NEW.
YOU'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

07:18.005 --> 07:20.741
OR YOU'LL BE GONE.

07:21.842 --> 07:23.143
JESUS CHRIST.

07:23.143 --> 07:25.746
YEAH.
AND HE WENT TO HOFSTRA.

07:26.613 --> 07:29.850
THIS IS BIG.
IT'S CRIMINAL.

07:29.850 --> 07:33.487
AND I WANT TO BE A PART
OF TREEING BOBBY AXELROD.

07:33.487 --> 07:34.855
HEY, I WANT TO BE
AN ASTRONAUT,

07:34.855 --> 07:37.524
BUT, UH, YOU KNOW,
I GET AIRSICK IN CHOPPY WEATHER.

07:37.524 --> 07:39.726
YOUR BURDEN OF PROOF
IS LOWER.

07:39.726 --> 07:40.861
THEY'LL TALK TO YOU

07:40.861 --> 07:43.797
BECAUSE THEY'RE HAPPY TO PAY
A FINE AND MOVE ON.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.032
I'M AT THE COALFACE.

07:45.032 --> 07:48.035
AND I REALLY DON'T APPRECIATE
YOU STROLLING IN HERE

07:48.035 --> 07:50.237
AND TELLING ME HOW TO DEPLOY
MY RESOURCES

07:50.237 --> 07:52.773
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T BUILD
YOUR OWN FUCKING CASE.

07:52.773 --> 07:54.474
I GET IT.
YOU GUYS ARE ROCK STARS.

07:54.474 --> 07:56.109
YEAH, WE GET IT.
YOU WANT TO BE ONE, TOO.

07:56.109 --> 07:57.678
NONE OF THAT MATTERS.

07:57.678 --> 08:00.781
UH, SPYROS, IF YOU'VE LOCKED ON
TO SOME TRAIL OF BREAD CRUMBS

08:00.781 --> 08:02.683
THAT LEADS
TO BOBBY AXELROD,

08:02.683 --> 08:04.117
THAT COULD BE A WIN
FOR EVERYONE.

08:04.117 --> 08:06.553
SO, LEAVE YOUR STUFF,
WE'LL TAKE A LOOK,

08:06.553 --> 08:09.022
AND WE'LL LET YOU KNOW
IF IT RISES TO THE LEVEL

08:09.022 --> 08:10.190
THAT WE CAN PROSECUTE,

08:10.190 --> 08:12.793
ONE THAT WON'T BE REVERSED
ON APPEAL.

08:12.793 --> 08:16.029
YOU KNOW, I UNDERSTAND
THE SOURCE OF YOUR RELUCTANCE.

08:16.029 --> 08:19.132
MM-HMM.
I HAVE A WIFE, TOO.

08:19.132 --> 08:20.601
BUT IT'S YOUR JOB --

08:20.601 --> 08:22.035
HEY, YOU GOT
YOUR ANSWER.

08:22.035 --> 08:23.036
WE'RE DONE.

08:26.740 --> 08:29.009
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

08:36.516 --> 08:38.685
[ SIGHS ]

08:51.965 --> 08:55.802
Bobby: I LOVED AND REMEMBER EACH
AND EVERY ONE OF YOUR FATHERS,

08:55.802 --> 08:58.005
SO I'M PROUD OF ALL OF YOU

08:58.005 --> 09:00.607
WHO ARE READY TO HEAD OFF
TO SCHOOL IN THE FALL.

09:00.607 --> 09:03.944
26 OF OURS
PUT THROUGH COLLEGE

09:03.944 --> 09:05.846
BY THE MEMORIAL FOUNDATION
SO FAR.

09:05.846 --> 09:07.981
AND THIS YEAR'S GROUP --
SO LET'S BRING THEM UP,

09:07.981 --> 09:10.884
AND LET'S GIVE THEM A ROUND OF
APPLAUSE FOR THEIR ACHIEVEMENT.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.686
FREDDIE AQUAFINO, OFF TO DUKE.

09:12.686 --> 09:14.121
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

09:17.557 --> 09:19.026
FREDDIE, FREDDIE.

09:19.026 --> 09:21.795
I TRADED SHOULDER TO SHOULDER
WITH YOUR FATHER.

09:21.795 --> 09:24.231
HE'D BE SO PROUD
OF YOU TODAY.

09:26.767 --> 09:28.869
FIRST YEAR'S TUITION
AND BOARD.

09:28.869 --> 09:30.604
ALL RIGHT, COME HERE.

09:30.604 --> 09:34.141
[ APPLAUSE ]

09:34.141 --> 09:36.710
THAT'S WHAT THIS
IS ALL ABOUT, GUYS.

09:36.710 --> 09:38.879
NOT ONLY HOW OUR FIRM
SURVIVED 9/11,

09:38.879 --> 09:41.148
BUT HOW WE DIDN'T GIVE UP.

09:41.148 --> 09:45.819
HOW WE COMMITTED TO EACH OTHER,
TO OUR FAMILY.

09:45.819 --> 09:49.056
AND I AM SO MOVED BY HOW WE'VE
ALL FLOURISHED TOGETHER.

09:49.056 --> 09:50.924
SOME FLOURISHING
MORE THAN OTHERS.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.893
[ ALL MURMURING ]

09:52.893 --> 09:56.863
IT'S JUST WRONG THAT YOU'RE
THE ONE STANDING THERE.

09:56.863 --> 09:58.031
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S ENOUGH.

09:58.031 --> 10:02.169
NO, NO. IT'S OKAY.
JUNE...

10:02.169 --> 10:03.904
I'D FEEL THE SAME WAY.

10:03.904 --> 10:05.973
I GET IT.

10:05.973 --> 10:08.608
YOU GOT TO BE THINKING,
"WHY WAS HE SPARED?

10:08.608 --> 10:10.677
WHY IS MY HUSBAND GONE?"

10:10.677 --> 10:12.713
FOR MONTHS
AFTER THE PLANES HIT,

10:12.713 --> 10:14.781
ALL I COULD DO
WAS ASK MYSELF WHY.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.285
WHY WAS I THE ONLY
SURVIVING PARTNER?

10:18.285 --> 10:19.286
WHY WASN'T I THERE?

10:19.286 --> 10:21.121
COULD -- COULD I HAVE DONE
SOMETHING?

10:21.121 --> 10:22.923
WHY WAS I THE ONLY ONE
OUT OF THE OFFICE

10:22.923 --> 10:24.224
ON MEETINGS THAT MORNING?

10:26.793 --> 10:29.696
WE'LL NEVER KNOW.

10:29.696 --> 10:31.631
SO I MADE UP MY OWN "WHY."

10:33.100 --> 10:34.835
BECAUSE OF YOU.

10:37.004 --> 10:38.672
YOU PUT IT ALL
ON YOUR BACK, BOBBY.

10:38.672 --> 10:40.774
[ APPLAUSE ]

10:40.774 --> 10:43.377
AM I THE GREATEST GUY
IN THE WORLD?

10:43.377 --> 10:44.778
HELL, NO.

10:44.778 --> 10:47.981
I JUST DID WHAT I KNEW THE
PARTNERS AND FRIENDS I'D LOST

10:47.981 --> 10:50.183
WOULD'VE DONE FOR MY FAMILY.

10:50.183 --> 10:52.386
WHAT YOUR HUSBAND
WOULD'VE DONE, JUNE.

10:54.388 --> 10:56.723
AND YOU KNOW I'M SORRY.

11:02.329 --> 11:06.266
'CAUSE I MISS RAKE EVERY DAY...

11:08.368 --> 11:11.338
...JUST AS MY BEAUTIFUL WIFE,
LARA,

11:11.338 --> 11:14.908
MISSES
HER HEROIC BROTHER DEAN.

11:18.412 --> 11:22.349
BOBBY AXELROD
IS MIKE TYSON IN HIS PRIME.

11:22.349 --> 11:25.419
AND YOU DO NOT WANT
MIKE TYSON IN HIS PRIME.

11:25.419 --> 11:27.921
REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED TO
THE GUYS WHO FOUGHT HIM THEN?

11:27.921 --> 11:29.456
YEAH, THEY GOT THEIR FACES
PUSHED IN.

11:29.456 --> 11:30.891
BUT EVENTUALLY
HE GOT BEAT.

11:30.891 --> 11:32.959
BUSTER DOUGLAS KNOCKED HIM
ON HIS ASS.

11:32.959 --> 11:33.960
RIGHT.
KETCHUP?

11:33.960 --> 11:36.063
"EVENTUALLY"
IS THE KEY WORD.

11:36.063 --> 11:38.298
WHEN TYSON
WAS READY TO GO.

11:38.298 --> 11:39.900
SINCE MY APPOINTMENT,

11:39.900 --> 11:42.235
THIS OFFICE IS UNDEFEATED
IN FINANCIAL PROSECUTIONS --

11:42.235 --> 11:43.336
81 AND 0.

11:43.336 --> 11:45.806
AND THAT'S BECAUSE I KNOW
WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT.

11:45.806 --> 11:49.076
I GET IT, BUT...
THIS WOULD BE A BIG ONE.

11:49.076 --> 11:52.079
BRYAN, WHAT DO YOU THINK
HAPPENED HERE THIS MORNING?

11:52.079 --> 11:54.714
WE GOT SIGNIFICANT
INFORMATION.

11:54.714 --> 11:58.218
MAYBE. OR MAYBE IT WAS SPYROS
SETTING US UP.

11:58.218 --> 12:02.389
NOW, WE GO IN FIRST
AND LOSE IN THE CRIMINAL ACTION,

12:02.389 --> 12:05.292
SPYROS IN THE S.E.C.
CAN STILL GET HIM CIVILLY.

12:05.292 --> 12:09.096
NOW, WE WIN, SPYROS WINS.
WE LOSE...

12:09.096 --> 12:10.831
SPYROS STILL FUCKING WINS.

12:10.831 --> 12:13.033
DAMN.
THE KETCHUP'S EMPTY.

12:13.033 --> 12:16.269
WE'VE GOT TO BE PLAYING
THREE-DIMENSIONAL CHESS.

12:16.269 --> 12:19.272
AXE IS A FOLK HERO
IN THIS TOWN.

12:19.272 --> 12:22.008
THE GUY GAVE THE NEW YORK CITY
FIREFIGHTER'S FOUNDATION

12:22.008 --> 12:24.945
$100 MILLION LAST YEAR.

12:24.945 --> 12:26.847
POLICE GAVE HIM A PLAQUE
AT GROUND ZERO

12:26.847 --> 12:28.215
WITH HIS GODDAMN NAME
ON IT.

12:28.215 --> 12:30.150
SPITZER'S NAME WAS ON ALL
THE HIGHWAY SIGNS, TOO.

12:30.150 --> 12:31.284
SIGNS COME DOWN.

12:32.319 --> 12:34.788
THAT'S WHY I LOVE YOU, MAN.

12:34.788 --> 12:38.925
BUT A GOOD MATADOR DOESN'T
TRY TO KILL A FRESH BULL.

12:40.393 --> 12:43.196
YOU WAIT UNTIL HE'S BEEN
STUCK A FEW TIMES.

12:45.198 --> 12:47.767
WE NEED AN OPENING,
HOWEVER SMALL.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.470
THEN WE GET THE GUY
THE MOMENT THAT HE'S GETTABLE,

12:50.470 --> 12:51.771
JUST LIKE THE OTHERS.

12:51.771 --> 12:54.241
BUT NOT IF THERE'S
A CHANCE WE LOSE.

12:56.943 --> 12:59.846
WHAT ABOUT...
THE OTHER ISSUE?

12:59.846 --> 13:02.482
THE ONE SPYROS MENTIONED --
HOME?

13:05.152 --> 13:06.486
WAS HE RIGHT ABOUT THAT?

13:08.054 --> 13:09.356
NO.

13:17.998 --> 13:19.933
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

13:19.933 --> 13:21.334
I-I DON'T...[ SIGHS ]

13:21.334 --> 13:23.303
YOU KNOW WHAT,
IT'S A TOUGH DAY
FOR EVERYONE.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.272
I DON'T KNOW WHAT --
OH!

13:25.272 --> 13:26.273
JUST...

13:26.273 --> 13:28.408
I JUST HAD TO SELL
THE OCEANIS.

13:28.408 --> 13:31.111
[ SIGHS ]

13:31.111 --> 13:32.946
RAKE JUST LOVED THAT BOAT.

13:32.946 --> 13:35.415
I AM SURE THAT'S WHY
IT UPSET YOU.

13:35.415 --> 13:37.884
YOU KNOW, ME,
I NEVER SET FOOT ON A YACHT

13:37.884 --> 13:39.419
UNTIL I STARTED
DATING BOBBY.

13:39.419 --> 13:40.554
IN INWOOD, GROWING UP,

13:40.554 --> 13:43.924
THE ONLY BOATING WE EVER DID
WAS THE STATEN ISLAND FERRY.

13:43.924 --> 13:45.425
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:45.425 --> 13:47.294
BIG IRISH FAMILY.
FIVE SIBS.

13:47.294 --> 13:49.829
CLOSE, THOUGH.

13:49.829 --> 13:52.098
FIREMEN, COPS, NURSES.

13:53.400 --> 13:55.468
THEN,
WHEN I MOVED UP HERE,

13:55.468 --> 13:59.172
THIS WORLD, I SAW
HOW EVERYONE LOOKED AT ME.

13:59.172 --> 14:01.174
I NEVER JUDGED.

14:01.174 --> 14:03.610
OF COURSE NOT.

14:05.345 --> 14:06.613
SO I GOT MY ACT TOGETHER.

14:06.613 --> 14:09.916
AND I'M COMFORTABLE
IN THIS LIFE.

14:09.916 --> 14:11.952
BUT CERTAIN THINGS
YOU LEARN IN INWOOD,

14:11.952 --> 14:13.954
THEY NEVER LEAVE YOU --
YOU KNOW, LIKE THE IDEA

14:13.954 --> 14:15.622
THAT IF SOMEONE
HAS A PROBLEM WITH YOU

14:15.622 --> 14:17.324
AND THEY COME TO YOU
IN PERSON,

14:17.324 --> 14:19.392
YOU DO WHAT YOU CAN
TO TAKE CARE OF IT.

14:19.392 --> 14:22.495
BUT IF THEY TAKE
THAT BEEF PUBLIC,

14:22.495 --> 14:25.999
THE GROUND JUST FALLS OUT FROM
BENEATH THEM WHERE I'M FROM.

14:25.999 --> 14:28.868
YOU FIND YOURSELF
ALL ALONE.

14:30.103 --> 14:32.038
ARE YOU THREATENING ME?

14:32.038 --> 14:33.273
[ SCOFFS ]

14:33.273 --> 14:35.242
YOU'RE FUCKING RIGHT I AM.

14:35.242 --> 14:38.044
IT'S HOW I GREW UP.

14:38.044 --> 14:39.613
[ SIREN WAILS ]

14:44.284 --> 14:45.652
EXCUSE ME, SIR?

14:45.652 --> 14:46.486
YES?

14:46.486 --> 14:47.621
I MAY BE SPEAKING
OUT OF TURN --

14:47.621 --> 14:49.422
I PROBABLY SHOULDN'T HAVE EVEN
BEEN IN THE ROOM

14:49.422 --> 14:50.890
WHERE AXELROD
WAS DISCUSSED --

14:50.890 --> 14:52.926
BUT YOU KNOW THE NORTON PLACE
OUT AT THE BEACH?

14:52.926 --> 14:54.327
WHY WOULD WE?
NOT YOU.
THE U.S. ATTORNEY.

14:54.327 --> 14:55.595
HIS FATHER'S HOUSE
IS AROUND THE JETTY.

14:55.595 --> 14:56.896
YES, I KNOW THE HOUSE.
WHAT?

14:56.896 --> 14:59.032
I JUST HEARD BOBBY AXELROD
IS TRYING TO BUY IT.

14:59.032 --> 15:02.035
â™ªâ™ª

15:09.442 --> 15:10.910
WHERE DID
YOU HEAR THAT?

15:10.910 --> 15:13.246
COURT CLERK'S COUSIN WORKS FOR
THE REALTOR AND MENTIONED IT.

15:13.246 --> 15:15.048
HOW MUCH?
$83 MILLION.

15:15.048 --> 15:16.483
REALLY?

15:16.483 --> 15:18.318
THAT WOULD BE
WIDELY REPORTED.

15:18.318 --> 15:19.653
WIDELY.

15:19.653 --> 15:21.955
PEOPLE HATE GUYS
WHO BUY THINGS LIKE THAT.

15:23.523 --> 15:25.158
[ SCOFFS ]

15:36.002 --> 15:39.439
I JUST LOST MY MOJO
SOMEWHERE ALONG THE LINE.

15:39.439 --> 15:41.708
IT'S FUCKING GONE.

15:41.708 --> 15:45.312
AND YOU'RE MRS. MOJO,
SO I BOOKED THE APPOINTMENT.

15:45.312 --> 15:47.113
IT'S DR. MOJO.

15:47.113 --> 15:48.548
RIGHT.

15:50.183 --> 15:52.519
I HEAR IT HAPPENS
TO GUYS MY AGE.

15:52.519 --> 15:54.688
MAYBE I'M DEPRESSED.

15:54.688 --> 15:57.991
MAYBE I SHOULD TRY
SOME PROZAC, EFFEXOR --

15:57.991 --> 15:59.993
UH-HUH.
WE'LL GET TO THAT.

15:59.993 --> 16:03.997
NOW, HAVE YOU BEEN EATING,
SLEEPING, EXERCISING?

16:03.997 --> 16:05.598
YEAH, MORE OR LESS.

16:05.598 --> 16:08.134
MAYBE NOT SO MUCH
WITH THE SLEEPING.

16:08.134 --> 16:10.503
AND THINGS WITH YOUR WIFE?

16:10.503 --> 16:11.705
OKAY, MOSTLY.

16:11.705 --> 16:13.340
SEX?

16:13.340 --> 16:14.708
NORMAL.

16:14.708 --> 16:16.710
I'VE BEEN MARRIED 10 YEARS,
SO...

16:16.710 --> 16:19.979
SO DOWN TO JUST
ONCE A DAY.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.715
SO, IT'S REALLY JUST
THE BOOK?

16:21.715 --> 16:24.384
I'M DOWN 4%...

16:24.384 --> 16:26.086
YEAR TO DATE.

16:26.086 --> 16:27.587
[ SIGHS ]

16:27.587 --> 16:29.656
EVERYONE ELSE
IS UP DOUBLE DIGITS.

16:31.358 --> 16:33.660
I'M DOWN.

16:33.660 --> 16:37.030
I'M FUCKED.
YOU DON'T NEED MEDS.

16:37.030 --> 16:39.299
YOU'RE JUST LISTENING
TO THE WRONG VOICE.

16:39.299 --> 16:41.368
YOU'RE TUNED INTO
THE ONE YELLING AT YOU

16:41.368 --> 16:43.670
OVER THE LOUDSPEAKER
THAT YOU'RE FUCKING STUPID

16:43.670 --> 16:46.306
AND YOUR PERFORMANCE
BLOWS.

16:46.306 --> 16:49.743
AND YOU'RE IGNORING
THE QUIET ONE INSIDE

16:49.743 --> 16:52.312
TELLING YOU
WHERE THE ALPHA IS.

16:52.312 --> 16:56.383
NOW, THAT'S THE VOICE
THAT GOT YOU HERE.

16:56.383 --> 16:59.519
AND IT'S STILL THERE
IF YOU'RE WILLING TO LISTEN.

17:01.020 --> 17:04.124
WHAT'S THAT VOICE
TELLING YOU?

17:05.191 --> 17:07.527
THAT EVEN THOUGH
I'VE STIFFED A FEW

17:07.527 --> 17:09.162
THAT I'M PRETTY DAMN GOOD.

17:09.162 --> 17:10.363
UNH-UNH.

17:10.363 --> 17:11.631
STAND UP.

17:11.631 --> 17:14.134
STAND UP.

17:16.069 --> 17:18.037
WHAT'D YOU TAKE DOWN
LAST YEAR?

17:18.037 --> 17:19.239
$7.2 MILLION.

17:19.239 --> 17:21.207
$7.2 MILLION.

17:22.809 --> 17:27.080
$7.2 MILL-- FEEL THAT.

17:28.448 --> 17:30.316
$7.2 MILLION.

17:30.316 --> 17:31.751
BRING IT CLOSE.

17:33.319 --> 17:34.721
[ Louder ] $7.2 MILLION.

17:34.721 --> 17:36.523
SO, WHAT'S IT SAYING?

17:36.523 --> 17:37.457
THAT I'M AWESOME.

17:37.457 --> 17:38.425
THERE YOU GO.

17:38.425 --> 17:40.460
AND WHAT DOES IT HAVE
TO SAY BACK

17:40.460 --> 17:42.429
TO THAT LOUD,
CRITICAL VOICE?

17:42.429 --> 17:43.463
IT'S SAYING, "FUCK YOU."

17:43.463 --> 17:45.064
GOOD!

17:45.064 --> 17:46.466
SIT DOWN.

17:48.601 --> 17:51.171
NOW, I WANT YOU TO GO BACK
TO YOUR BLOOMBERG

17:51.171 --> 17:54.073
AND CUT BAIT ON YOUR LOSERS --
YOU KNOW THE ONES.

17:54.073 --> 17:55.341
THE ONES YOU'VE BEEN
DEFENDING,

17:55.341 --> 17:56.476
HOPING
THEY'LL COME 'ROUND,

17:56.476 --> 17:57.710
BUT, SECRETLY,
YOU KNOW NEVER WILL.

17:57.710 --> 17:59.546
I WANT YOU
TO JUST COMMIT

17:59.546 --> 18:02.081
THAT YOU'RE IN IT
FOR THE LONG HAUL,

18:02.081 --> 18:03.483
THAT YOU WILL SUCCEED.

18:03.483 --> 18:05.718
AND ONCE YOU DO THAT,
THE NEW IDEAS,

18:05.718 --> 18:07.821
THE WINNERS,
WILL PRESENT THEMSELVES

18:07.821 --> 18:10.223
BECAUSE YOU ARE A WINNER.

18:10.223 --> 18:12.459
YOU'RE IN THE SPECIAL FORCES
HERE.

18:12.459 --> 18:14.828
YOU ARE A NAVY SEAL.

18:14.828 --> 18:16.229
AND THERE'S A REASON
FOR THAT.

18:16.229 --> 18:18.798
DID THE S.E.A.L.s MAKE A MISTAKE
SIGNING YOU UP?

18:18.798 --> 18:20.600
[ Chuckling ] NO.
THEY DID NOT.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.268
THE S.E.A.L.s
DON'T MAKE MISTAKES.

18:24.170 --> 18:25.505
[ SIGHS ]

18:25.505 --> 18:28.408
SO GET OUT THERE
AND DO WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.278
WE HAVE TO STOP HERE.

18:55.668 --> 18:57.237
HELLO, GUYS.

18:57.237 --> 18:58.204
DADDY!

18:58.204 --> 18:59.239
OH, HOW ARE YOU?
HM?

18:59.239 --> 19:00.807
HOW WAS SCHOOL?
WHAT'D YOU GET UP TO?

19:00.807 --> 19:02.475
IT WAS BORING.
IT WAS BORING.

19:02.475 --> 19:04.444
BORING. FANTASTIC.
MONEY WELL SPENT.

19:04.444 --> 19:06.479
[ BOTH GIGGLE ]
THOSE GO OFF
AFTER DINNER, OKAY?

19:06.479 --> 19:07.614
OKAY!

19:07.614 --> 19:08.581
HEY, BABE.

19:08.581 --> 19:10.183
HI, HONEY.

19:10.183 --> 19:11.784
WHAT ARE YOU WORKING ON?

19:11.784 --> 19:13.319
JUST SESSION NOTES.

19:13.319 --> 19:14.487
[ CHUCKLES ] OH.

19:14.487 --> 19:17.624
WALL-TO-WALL OEDIPAL COMPLEXES
MAKING THEM ALL GO LIMP?

19:17.624 --> 19:18.725
PFFT!

19:18.725 --> 19:20.894
YOU HAVE AN AMAZING
UNDERSTANDING OF PEOPLE.

19:20.894 --> 19:22.395
WHAT ARE
WE DRINKING, HERE?

19:22.395 --> 19:24.163
THE USUAL.
MMM.

19:24.163 --> 19:25.598
HOW'S CRIME FIGHTING?

19:25.598 --> 19:27.367
THE USUAL.

19:29.736 --> 19:31.804
MM.

19:31.804 --> 19:34.307
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

19:36.776 --> 19:39.345
YOU GOOD
WITH YOUR SITUATION?

19:39.345 --> 19:42.348
I KNOW YOU SAID YOU MIGHT'VE
BEEN FEELING BORED A WHILE BACK.

19:42.348 --> 19:45.685
THAT'S NOT
EXACTLY WHAT I SAID.

19:45.685 --> 19:46.853
HMM.

19:46.853 --> 19:50.890
YOU SAID, UH, YOU WEREN'T SURE
IF YOU WERE STILL GROWING.

19:50.890 --> 19:54.193
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

19:54.193 --> 19:56.362
I WAS TALKING
TO THE HEAD COUNSEL OF G.E.,

19:56.362 --> 19:58.698
AND THEY'RE LOOKING
FOR A NEW HEAD OF H.R.

19:58.698 --> 20:00.567
I CAN PUT IN THE WORD
IF YOU WANT IT.

20:00.567 --> 20:02.835
UH...

20:02.835 --> 20:05.471
IS THERE S--

20:05.471 --> 20:08.575
IS THERE SOME REASON
I CAN'T KEEP DOING MY JOB?

20:08.575 --> 20:09.976
NO.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

20:11.778 --> 20:13.880
I HEARD ABOUT A POSITION,
SO I PRESENTED IT.

20:15.582 --> 20:17.750
DON'T YOU GET ENOUGH
OF MOVING THE PIECES

20:17.750 --> 20:18.952
AROUND THE BOARD AT WORK?

20:18.952 --> 20:21.688
OKAY. YOU DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT OPPORTUNITIES, FINE.

20:21.688 --> 20:23.823
ARE YOU PROSECUTING
SOMEBODY AT AXE?

20:23.823 --> 20:24.958
WHAT'S GOING ON, CHUCK?

20:24.958 --> 20:26.659
FIRST OFF, NO.

20:26.659 --> 20:29.896
AND SECOND, YOU KNOW
THAT WE DON'T DISCUSS THAT.

20:29.896 --> 20:32.432
SO QUIT YOUR FUCKING JOB.

20:36.803 --> 20:39.272
HEY, KEV, WILL YOU TAKE
YOUR SISTER UPSTAIRS

20:39.272 --> 20:40.506
AND, UH, START THE BATH?

20:40.506 --> 20:42.375
I'LL BE UP
IN A MINUTE, OKAY?

20:44.877 --> 20:46.679
THANK YOU.

20:46.679 --> 20:48.448
TAKE IT EASY, OKAY?

20:48.448 --> 20:51.250
I'M THE GODDAMN
U.S. ATTORNEY, WENDY.

20:51.250 --> 20:53.753
SO? I'VE BEEN WORKING THERE
SINCE BEFORE WE WERE MARRIED

20:53.753 --> 20:55.555
AND LONG BEFORE
YOU WERE IN OFFICE.

20:55.555 --> 20:57.724
LOOK, NOT
THAT WE'RE THERE,

20:57.724 --> 21:01.427
BUT WE DID ALWAYS DISCUSS
THAT THE DAY MIGHT COME

21:01.427 --> 21:03.429
WHEN THERE WAS A CONFLICT.

21:03.429 --> 21:05.798
THAT WAS BEFORE I WAS MAKING
EIGHT TIMES WHAT YOU MAKE.

21:05.798 --> 21:08.868
AND BEFORE YOU STARTED MAKING
CHUCK SR. PLAYS LIKE THIS.

21:08.868 --> 21:11.537
LEAVE HIM OUT OF IT.
OKAY?

21:11.537 --> 21:13.506
AND WHO MAKES MORE MONEY?
REALLY?

21:13.506 --> 21:15.942
IS THIS, UH, WHAT
WE'RE TEACHING THE KIDS?

21:15.942 --> 21:17.510
OH, ARE WE TEACHING THEM
THAT DADDY'S JOB

21:17.510 --> 21:18.645
IS ALWAYS MORE IMPORTANT
THAT MOMMY'S?

21:18.645 --> 21:20.446
I WORK FOR THE PUBLIC GOOD.

21:20.446 --> 21:22.715
NO, YOU WORK FOR THE GOOD
OF CHUCK RHOADES.

21:22.715 --> 21:24.651
MAYBE SOMETIMES
THEY INTERSECT.

21:24.651 --> 21:26.019
OH, MY GOD.

21:26.019 --> 21:28.688
WOULD YOU TURN OFF
YOUR FUCKING SHRINK SWITCH?

21:28.688 --> 21:29.789
[ SIGHS ]

21:31.991 --> 21:33.860
MM-HMM.

21:33.860 --> 21:35.928
LET'S TAKE THIS DOWN
A NOTCH.

21:37.830 --> 21:40.433
YEAH.

21:42.368 --> 21:44.504
I JUST -- I DON'T KNOW
WHERE ALL THIS IS COMING FROM,

21:44.504 --> 21:46.372
AND YOU KNOW I DON'T LIKE
TO BE MANIPULATED.

21:46.372 --> 21:47.306
I'M NOT MANIPULATING.

21:47.306 --> 21:48.608
NOT THAT THAT'S
WHAT YOU WERE DOING,

21:48.608 --> 21:49.709
BUT THAT'S WHAT I FELT LIKE.

21:51.477 --> 21:54.013
AND OF COURSE
YOUR JOB'S IMPORTANT.

21:54.013 --> 21:55.515
YOU'RE A SUPERHERO.

22:01.320 --> 22:03.623
AND I'M SUPER PROUD
OF YOU.

22:03.623 --> 22:05.892
BUT MY THING
MATTERS TO ME, TOO.

22:05.892 --> 22:09.062
OF COURSE.

22:09.062 --> 22:11.597
YOU'RE KILLING IT.

22:18.571 --> 22:21.441
[ DOG BARKING ]

22:23.576 --> 22:25.712
WHOA! WHOA, WHOA!
WATCH IT, THERE, ELMO!

22:25.712 --> 22:26.979
NO! GET DOWN, BOY!

22:26.979 --> 22:28.347
EASY, BIG GUY.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.515
[ DOG BARKING ]

22:29.515 --> 22:31.084
Bobby: AH, LET HIM BE.
HEY, LET HIM BE.

22:31.084 --> 22:32.919
LET HIM BE. IT'S OKAY.
LET HIM GO FREE.

22:32.919 --> 22:35.388
[ ELMO BARKING, WHINING ]

22:35.388 --> 22:36.589
HE'S A LIVE WIRE,
THAT ONE.

22:36.589 --> 22:38.357
OOH, YEAH.
HE CHEWED UP A CUSTOM SOFA.

22:38.357 --> 22:39.692
WE'VE GOT TO
CALM HIM DOWN.

22:39.692 --> 22:40.793
SEND HIM
TO OBEDIENCE SCHOOL.

22:40.793 --> 22:42.528
HE'S GOING TO THE VET
TO GET FIXED.

22:42.528 --> 22:43.596
OOH.

22:43.596 --> 22:44.630
ENJOY, GUYS.

22:44.630 --> 22:46.466
ALL RIGHT, BOYS.
WHAT DO WE SAY TO CHEF RYAN?

22:46.466 --> 22:47.734
Both: THANK YOU!

22:49.969 --> 22:52.138
BOYS, BOYS, LOOK.
LOOK. LOOK AT THIS.

22:52.138 --> 22:54.841
LOOK, LOOK.
HE'S MARKING HIS TERRITORY.

22:54.841 --> 22:56.609
HE'S PEEING
ON THE FURNITURE.

22:56.609 --> 22:59.412
YEAH. YEAH, BUT HE'S SHOWING
RYAN WHO'S BOSS.

22:59.412 --> 23:00.880
THAT'S WHY IT'S CALLED
A PISSING CONTEST

23:00.880 --> 23:02.648
WHEN TWO MEN TRY
AND STAKE OUT THEIR TURF.

23:02.648 --> 23:04.784
I DON'T LOVE IT
WHEN MEN DO THAT, EITHER.

23:04.784 --> 23:06.919
Woman:
ELMO, OUTSIDE NOW!

23:06.919 --> 23:09.889
COME ON. POOR GUY.

23:09.889 --> 23:13.526
DEAN, SEVENTH PRESIDENT.
HINT -- TWO AFTER MONROE.

23:13.526 --> 23:15.595
JACKSON.
ANDREW JACKSON.

23:15.595 --> 23:16.829
GORDIE,
WHERE WAS HE FROM?

23:16.829 --> 23:18.564
LET'S TALK YANKEES.

23:18.564 --> 23:21.100
'CAUSE YOU DON'T KNOW.
DON'T SWITCH THE SUBJECT.

23:21.100 --> 23:22.401
I DO KNOW.

23:22.401 --> 23:23.436
PROVE IT.

23:23.436 --> 23:25.171
SEATTLE?

23:25.171 --> 23:27.406
THERE WAS NO SEATTLE
BACK THEN, IDIOT.

23:27.406 --> 23:28.674
I BET I'LL GET IT
ON THE NEXT GUESS.

23:28.674 --> 23:29.742
BET YOU DON'T.

23:29.742 --> 23:30.409
HOW MUCH?

23:30.409 --> 23:31.477
10 PUSH-UPS.

23:31.477 --> 23:32.779
DEAL.

23:32.779 --> 23:35.481
BORDER AREAS
NEAR THE CAROLINAS.

23:35.481 --> 23:36.516
[ BOBBY AND LARA LAUGH ]

23:36.516 --> 23:39.118
YOU CAN'T FALL FOR THAT
EVERY TIME, DEAN.

23:39.118 --> 23:41.988
SEE, HE KNOWS HIS CUSTOMER,
AND HE SETS YOU UP.

23:41.988 --> 23:45.091
HE'S WILLING TO LOOK FOOLISH
SHORT-TERM TO WIN LONG-TERM.

23:45.091 --> 23:46.793
YOU GOT TO
REMEMBER THAT.

23:46.793 --> 23:49.729
AND, GORDIE,
DON'T SUCKER YOUR BROTHER.

23:49.729 --> 23:51.831
ALL RIGHT, COME ON.
PAY YOUR BET.

23:51.831 --> 23:53.599
WE DON'T WELSH.

23:53.599 --> 23:55.601
[ SIGHS ]

23:55.601 --> 23:56.769
SEE WHAT YOU GOT.

23:58.471 --> 24:01.974
All: ONE. TWO.

24:01.974 --> 24:02.975
LOWER.

24:02.975 --> 24:04.477
THREE.

24:04.877 --> 24:07.947
â™ªâ™ª

24:18.624 --> 24:20.092
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

24:23.162 --> 24:25.064
[ SNIFFS ]

24:25.064 --> 24:27.466
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

24:27.466 --> 24:29.068
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

24:29.068 --> 24:31.804
KIM: Sir? The Leniency
Conference starts in 10 minutes.

24:36.909 --> 24:37.944
AFTERNOON.

24:40.680 --> 24:42.949
THANK YOU FOR AGREEING
TO SEE US.

24:42.949 --> 24:44.817
WHAT THE FUCK ARE
YOU DOING HERE, DAD?

24:44.817 --> 24:46.552
TRYING TO GET ME
DISBARRED?

24:46.552 --> 24:49.822
CHRIST. YOU'RE MORE DRAMATIC
THAN YOUR MOTHER.

24:49.822 --> 24:52.758
Attorney: WE ARE NOT BREAKING
ANY RULES OR REGULATIONS.

24:52.758 --> 24:55.561
MR. RHOADES IS NOT BEING
COMPENSATED TO APPEAR HERE.

24:55.561 --> 24:57.864
OH, I KNOW
HOW CAREFUL HE IS...

24:57.864 --> 24:59.498
AND WHY YOU BROUGHT HIM.

24:59.498 --> 25:01.634
BUT BELIEVE ME,
IT'S ALREADY BACKFIRED.

25:01.634 --> 25:03.703
HEAR US OUT.

25:03.703 --> 25:05.738
SKIP KNOWS
THAT HE DID WRONG.

25:05.738 --> 25:07.206
NOW THAT HE'S BEEN,
UH, CONVICTED, SURE.

25:07.206 --> 25:09.008
BUT WHEN HE HAD A CHANCE
TO PLEAD OUT...

25:09.008 --> 25:10.142
THAT'S THE PAST.

25:10.142 --> 25:13.279
RIGHT NOW, WE ARE TRYING
TO SET SOMETHING UP

25:13.279 --> 25:16.883
THAT WILL ALLOW SKIP
TO SHOW HIS REHABILITATION

25:16.883 --> 25:20.620
AND FOR HIM TO CONTRIBUTE
TO SOCIETY.

25:20.620 --> 25:22.588
BY WHAT?
OH, I KNOW.

25:22.588 --> 25:24.156
UH, PAYING A BIGGER FINE

25:24.156 --> 25:27.026
IN EXCHANGE
FOR REDUCED JAIL TIME?

25:27.026 --> 25:31.564
WHAT ARE WE TALKING ABOUT,
UH, $5 MILLION?

25:31.564 --> 25:32.899
WE WERE GOING TO
SUGGEST $10 MILLION

25:32.899 --> 25:34.233
IN EXCHANGE
FOR HOUSE ARREST.

25:34.233 --> 25:37.069
WHICH REPRESENTS A FAR MORE
REASONABLE SETTLEMENT THAN --

25:37.069 --> 25:38.938
MM-HMM. YEAH.
SO, THAT WAY,

25:38.938 --> 25:41.841
INSTEAD OF WORRYING ABOUT
ACTUALLY GOING TO PRISON,

25:41.841 --> 25:43.709
YOU CAN GET RIGHT TO
DOING CHARITABLE WORKS

